properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from Cape Mendocino to Pt. Arena CA out 10 nm
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 14 at 8:32PM PST until January 16 at 12:00AM PST by NWS Eureka CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, south winds 10 to 20 kt
with gusts up to 30 kt and seas 10 to 12 feet. For the Gale
Warning, south winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts to 40 kt and seas 13
to 15 feet.

* WHERE...Cape Mendocino to Pt Arena out 10 nm.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 4 PM Wednesday to midnight
PST Wednesday night. For the Small Craft Advisory, until 4 PM
PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST WEDNESDAY... ...GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM WEDNESDAY TO MIDNIGHT PST WEDNESDAY NIGHT
